Make a directory called ~/.xmonad
Place the file named .xmonad.hs in ~/.xmonad
Copy the file xmobarrc to ~/.xmobarrc
Depending on the computer being used, the entries for Wireless or Network may be removed

CHROMEBOOK SPECIFIC:

Put chromebook in developer mode, download crouton installer
http://goo.gl/fd3zc

Pull up terminal in chrome:
CTRL-ALT T

Enter a linux shell
crosh> shell

sh ~/Downloads/crouton -r trusty -t audio -t xiwi -t x11 -t lxde-desktop -t lxde -t audio -t unity-desktop -t extension

CTRL-ALT T
crosh> shell
$ sudo enter-chroot

Now install the config using install.sh as normal
